observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the City Accountant and the City Budget Officer:
require all End-User Units to submit all documents for the procurement of goods and services charged from the current year appropriation, the obligations of the suppliers having been duly fulfilled, based on the contract, during the current year, to facilitate the recording of the related inventory and  expense accounts in the books  of the City;
record all valid claims chargeable against the appropriations in the year the expenses were incurred in the books of accounts of the City and to recognize payables for all unpaid expenditures as of year-end;
refrain from recognizing as Prior Period Adjustments  unrecorded received deliveries on procurement transactions from the previous years, likewise those received in the current year, to afford fair presentation of the affected accounts in the financial statements; and
henceforth, enforce strict compliance to the rules and regulations prescribed under Section 350 of R.A. 7160, Section 119 of P.D. No. 1445 and the relevant provisions of IPSAS 1, 3 and 19.

We recommended that the City Mayor:
direct all Accountable Officers with unliquidated balances to immediately liquidate their outstanding cash advances;
require the City Accountant to issue Certification that previous cash advances have been liquidated and accounted for in the books before granting cash advances pursuant to COA Circular No. 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012.

We recommended that the City Mayor require the General Services Officer to:
submit explanation on the late renewal of LTO Registration of the 80 Motor Vehicles;
identify the persons responsible for the delayed registration/non-registration and instruct them to refund the penalties incurred, otherwise, a Notice of Disallowance will be issued, seven (7) days after the receipt of this AOM;
conduct a physical count of all Motor Vehicles and identify the 225 vehicles whose registration were not yet renewed and exert best efforts to have these renewed if still serviceable;
exert effort to have the registration of the KIDS Bus transferred in the name of the LGU; and
improve the LGU’s system on the processing of LTO registration such that payments for smoke testing and motor vehicle insurance are obtained easily.

We recommended that the City Accountant:

review and reconcile monthly the Local DRRM Fund Utilization Reports with the accounting records to ensure proper monitoring of the available and utilized Local DRRM Funds and reflect reliable information in the said report;

coordinate with the City Budget Office to confirm the proper charging of disbursements from the Local DRRM Fund based on the RAO maintained by that office;

update the available Local DRRM Fund balance and include additional appropriations based on approved budget realignments and reversions; and

ensure that amounts in the Utilization Report are correctly summarized and reflected in the Notes to Financial Statements to provide a reliable disclosure of the Local DRRM Fund balance at the end of the year.

We recommended that the City Accountant:

Verify the prior years’ accounts to identify the causes of the variance of ₱54.9 million and ₱17 million and make the necessary adjustment, to reflect the correct balances of the reciprocal accounts;



Coordinate with the City Treasurer’s Office to identify the discrepancies noted in the accounts of delinquent taxpayers and make the necessary adjustment in the receivable accounts of the City to reflect the correct amount in the books.
